[Course_Description]
It's been a tough year of work for all of us. We've established new routines and ways to connect with our fellow employees. HR departments have shifted policy and engaged with workforces in ways they never imagined. As we move back into offices, new challenges await. In this course, instructor Pat Wadors guides you through determining what will work best for your organization. Pat addresses balancing productivity pressures with employee expectations, then explains how belonging can lead to comfort, connection, contribution, and co-creation. She goes over how to restructure work in ways that help employees feel their best and perform their best. Pat describes ways to develop in your workforce the resiliency, creativity, emotional skills, and more that they will need. She concludes by discussing HRâ€™s growing role in delivering greater business value and helping organizations and employees to adapt.